<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-04-09T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-04-09T08:00:00-05:00" n="193" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d193">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Mutual Guarantee (Eastern
                            Locarno)/122: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wiley</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-09T16:00:00+03:00">April 9,
                                    1935—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received April 9—2:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>138. According to information received from Lithuanian Minister, Litvinov
                            yesterday formally asked Estonian and Latvian Ministers to inform him
                            within 2 days whether their Governments would be willing to enter into a
                            pact of automatic mutual assistance together with the Soviet Union,
                            France, Czechoslovakia and Lithuania. Lithuania he said had no other
                            alternative but to enter such a pact. He did not indicate, however,
                            whether Lithuania would do so independently of the other two Baltic
                            States. He expressed concern over Polish influence on Estonian foreign
                            policy.</p>
                        <p>Repeated Riga.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wiley</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>